  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6573 sitting between the negative gamma wall at 6550 (-13.7B) and positive gamma resistance at 6580 (+16.7B), dealers are currently in equilibrium but biased toward buying any dip given the PIN regime. The massive positive gamma cluster from 6580-6600 (totaling ~50B) creates a formidable resistance zone where dealers will aggressively sell rallies, while the 6550 level acts as a magnet where dealer buying should provide support. The recent GEX surge combined with spot trading below the 6598 flip point suggests dealers are positioned to dampen volatility and create range-bound action between these key levels.\n\n**Key strikes to watch:** 6550 (buy support), 6580-6600 (sell resistance), 6598 (regime flip).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6550-6580 with dealers capping upside moves.",
